				\begin{document}$d_{b}$\end{document}, has only a small impact on the spectra, especially at the low spherical-harmonic degrees that will be resolved by the Psyche mission. Wieczorek (2018) also demonstrated that different assumptions about the directions of magnetization would affect the magnitude of the power spectrum by no more than a factor of about two. The two parameters that have the largest effect on the shape of the spectra are the radii of the magnetized disks, θ0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
